== How Gamma Differs From Talsia ==
[[File:Gammasector.jpg|thumb|right|260px|The Gamma Sector — a frontier beyond the warfront.]]

Before diving into strategy, it is critical to understand how Gamma fundamentally differs from the [[Talsian Warfront]]:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Aspect !! Talsian Warfront !! Gamma Sector
|-
| '''Structure''' || Linear — missions, sectors, TRP milestones || Non-linear — four quadrants, open patrol, self-directed
|-
| '''Mercs''' || Hired per mission, released after || Persist for the entire patrol; losing them costs Accolades
|-
| '''Winning strategy''' || "Tank everything" — high shields, drain, survive || Speed and fire rate dominate; high shields invite BM penalties
|-
| '''BM''' || Higher is generally better (more base BM = more income) || '''Diminishing returns above 30M''' — XP penalty scales up harshly at 37M+
|-
| '''Death risk''' || Low (with good deflection) || High — you '''will''' lose bots if you misclick or fight the wrong enemy
|-
| '''Goals''' || Clear and structured (TRP, mission counts, awards) || Vague and self-defined — quests, chassis, currencies, levels
|-
| '''Information''' || Documented and stable || Scarce; quest info is randomised each set; read everything in-game
|}

=== The Most Important Difference: Be Flexible ===

In Talsia, there is a well-documented optimal path: get TRP, buy Plasma Tech, get AMFDs, reach Alpha, push BM. You could follow a guide step-by-step and be fine.

'''Gamma does not work like that.'''

The guide below will give you a starting framework, but treat it as a ''rough map'', not a GPS route. Your goals will shift mid-patrol. The currency you planned to farm might take twice as long as expected. A bad fight might mean your mercs are gone. An unexpected quest trigger might redirect your entire patrol.

{{MessageBox
| header = Golden Rule of Gamma
| text   = '''Do what works for you.''' The top-ranked Controllers in Gamma will never share their exact strategies — and with good reason. The zone rewards inventiveness and adaptation. Use this guide as a starting point, explore aggressively, and build your own understanding.
}}

