== The Philosophy of Gamma ==

Gamma was '''designed to be a high-risk, high-reward zone'''. The developer's explicit intent is that Controllers who rely on slow, invincible deflection builds will be penalised — both in experience rewards (via the BM penalty above 30M) and in actual combat (Wasps and high-fire-rate enemies will drain you before you respond if your squad is slow).

Key principles to internalise:
* '''Speed wins.''' Going first is everything. [[Wasp]] enemies (base speed 225) will drain your reactors before you fire if you can't outpace them. [[Hornet|Hornets]] and high-uplink [[Seer]] builds are essential.
* '''Read everything.''' Gamma is full of quest text, in-game hints, and lore. Quest steps are gated on reading specific event text. Missing a Knight's name or city name means spending more KC hunting it down again.
* '''BM is a liability.''' In Talsia, high BM meant more reward. In Gamma, high BM means more Wasps, harder squads, and an XP penalty above 30M. '''Target ~20–30M BM''' for optimal Gamma rewards.
* '''Mercs are permanent (and precious).''' A Gamma merc you hire at the Epsilon FOB stays until it dies or you return to the workshop. Losing a full merc loadout to a bad fight is devastating. Don't over-commit valuable mercs to unnecessary fights.
* '''Note-taking is mandatory.''' Quest keys (Knight names, city names, door codes) are randomly generated each set. There is no in-game journal. Write them down immediately.

