== Prerequisites & Pre-Gamma Preparation ==
[[File:Spider.png|right|80px|Reaper chassis]]

Before entering Gamma, you should have completed the following in [[Talsian Warfront|Talsia]]:

=== Hard Requirements ===
* '''18,000 TRP''' (unlocks the [[Raven]] chassis — the defining bot of Gamma; can be slightly higher in some configurations)
* '''[[Advanced Multi-Fire Director|AMFDs]]''' equipped on your squad — this is the Talsia Alpha-sector endgame configuration
* Sufficient cash to purchase the 9th-bot Workshop upgrade (typically 25–100M credits) and at least one or two [[Raven]] chassis (25M each)
* Some Accolades reserves for the Epsilon FOB — you will start spending Accolades almost immediately on mercs

=== Strongly Recommended ===
* At least 3–5 [[DAX Pod]] modules — these provide drain deflection that is disproportionately valuable in early Gamma when enemy drain is your biggest threat
* Familiarity with managing [[KCharge]] efficiently — Gamma fights can cost significantly more KC than late-Talsia fights if you're unprepared

{{MessageBox
| header = On Entering Gamma Without Ravens
| text   = It is technically possible to enter Gamma with a Talsia squad (Crusaders, Seers, Reaper, CySentinel). However, Gamma enemies are tuned for late-game squads. Doing so will result in very high KC costs, significant bot attrition, and slow progress. The [[Raven]] is the practical minimum for comfortable Gamma play.
}}

