== Vulcore Cash Run ==
[[File:Varena.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Vulcore's Lava Fields — revisited for the cash you need.]]

Before or during your transition into Gamma, you will need a large amount of credits (typically '''100–200M''') to fund:
* The 9th-bot Workshop upgrade
* One or two [[Raven]] chassis (25M each)
* Initial equipment purchases

The most reliable way to obtain this is a '''Vulcore cash farming patrol''' with your late-game Talsia squad:

=== Vulcore Cash Run Strategy ===

# Take your standard AMFD squad into [[Vulcore Plain|Vulcore]]
# '''Inflate your BM as much as possible''' before entering — more BM means more credits from Azras
# '''Do not forget the [[Storm Shield]]''' — toss it on your [[Reaper]] or [[Leviathan|Levi]] to avoid being completely drained mid-patrol
# At the start of patrol: hire an [[Orbie]] merc; locate [[Azra's Arena]] as quickly as possible
# EX-series enemy squads give large experience and cash bonuses — pursue these
# More [[DAX Pod]] modules on your squad helps survive early encounters in Gamma later, so if you still need to purchase them, do so
# Farm [[Magma Lord]] encounters for additional [[Mercred|Mercreds]] — you can also ask Azra for coordinates to new Lava Fields if it's available again
# When you reach 50M credits: exit patrol, buy the Workshop upgrade, add a Seer for more BM, then '''re-enter for the next 50M'''

{{MessageBox
| header = Note on Vulcore Cash Nerfing
| text   = Vulcore cash rewards are reduced by ~25% for squads above a certain BM threshold (has changed over sets). The return trip is still worth it — just be aware that diminishing returns kick in as BM climbs very high.
}}

