=== Patrol 1 Walkthrough ===
[[File:Forcereconscreen2.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Praetorian Recon — fast, aggressive, and dangerous. Withdraw early if your squad isn't ready.]]

'''At the Epsilon FOB (start of patrol):'''
# Hire: 1× [[Custodian]] → 3× [[Nightowl]] → 1× [[Custodian]] (adjust Custodian count based on your projected shield needs — fewer if you are confident your CySentinel is sufficient; add [[Vamper]] mercs if you need more drain)
# Note your current Accolade balance — spend wisely. Merc costs add up fast.

'''NE Quadrant:'''
# On your way NE: '''pick up the free Drainer merc''' if found (it will appear as a special event; do not miss it)
# Head SE first to get the Enhanced Reaper city name from an SE Outpost (Step 1 of Enhanced Reaper quest — ~10% chance per outpost)
# While in SE: also look for the '''Brotherhood Knight's name''' (PMC Quest Step 1 — same ~10% chance per SE Outpost — this is a different piece of info from the Enhanced Reaper city name)
# Record: '''Brotherhood Outpost PIN, Brotherhood Knight name, PMC City name, Enhanced Reaper city name''' — write these down, they are one-time events
# Return to NE; head to the '''Horus Temple'''
# At the temple: find inscriptions → record the '''Brotherhood door code''' (PMC Quest Step 3)
# Look for the '''portal''' inside the temple (only appears if you already found the Enhanced Reaper city name from SE — if not, the portal won't show)
# If portal is available: enter, select the correct city, win 3 battles → receive the [[Enhanced Reaper]]
# Find the '''Matriarch''' in NE → she will give you the '''PMC city name''' (Quest Step 2 — only works after you have the Knight name from SE)
# Farm NE for '''3× Plutonium Core''' from the NE Trader (costs Mirons)
# If a '''Prius''' merc appears during NE patrol: hire it — Prius is required to unlock the [[Terminus Prototype]] chassis trader

'''SW Quadrant:'''
# Head to SW; find a '''Lava Fort''' — defeat it to earn the '''Coin of Destiny''' (PMC Quest Step 4; only the FIRST Lava Fort victory gives the Coin)
# Farm SW Caves and Lava Forts for '''Lava Diamonds''' — target 500 diamonds minimum (~39 diamonds per 1,800 KC in SW Caves; Forts give variable amounts)
# At the SW Trader: buy '''2× Hyper Drive''' (costs Lava Diamonds)
# If time and Diamonds allow: farm an additional 400+ Diamonds for later
# Note: Lava Fort fights include Lava Reapers — bring drain weapons; these fights cost 3–4 KC each if you're not prepared

'''NW Quadrant:'''
# With the Coin of Destiny in hand: locate the '''Brotherhood Outpost''' in NW (appears only if you have the Coin)
# Enter the Outpost; use the correct door code; select the '''correct Knight''' (the one whose name matches the SE intel)
# The Knight joins the squad for free — this triggers access to the Airfield
# Find the '''Airfield / Space Port''' in NW; have the Knight pilot the ship to the Horus Planet (PMC Quest Step 6)
# On the Horus Planet: find the city matching the NE Matriarch's info; learn the PMC was stolen; raze the Pirate Outpost → receive [[Peace Maker Cannon]] (Quest Step 9)
# Optional: buy 1× [[Rayden Device]] from the NW Trader (costs Accolades — 10,000) if available
# Farm Destroyers and Battle Cruisers in NW for TRP and Accolades if you need them

'''At 750 Lava Diamonds (milestone):'''
# Return to NE; trigger the '''Voice Calling for Help''' event (appears around 750 Diamonds threshold)
# Release the trapped unit → recruit the [[Prius]] merc (if not already hired)
# With Prius in squad: locate the '''Termi Chassis Trader''' in NE and purchase the [[Terminus Prototype]] chassis
# While searching for the trader: continue purchasing Plutonium Cores

'''Return to Base:'''
# Exchange collected Lava Diamonds → [[Miron|Mirons]] (via the Base currency exchanger)
# Buy '''3× [[FS14]]''' modules (costs Mirons)
# Exchange remaining Mirons → Accolades as needed for future merc costs
# In SE: buy '''7× [[Pneumatron|Pneu Reactors]]''' from the SE Trader
# In NW: buy [[Rayden Device|Raydens]] from the NW Trader until you have 3 total (1 from Talsia, 2 from Gamma's NW Market)

=== Optional: SW Arena ===
The '''Carnutum Ignus Arena''' Masters fight in SW is available at any point. Defeating the Arena Masters earns the '''[[Hydroplasmonic Reactor]]'''. This fight is '''[[#SW Arena Masters|detailed further below]]''' — completing it in Patrol 1 is viable if you're confident in your squad, but you're most likely going to get wiped

