== Dangerous Enemies & Things to Watch Out For ==
[[File:Piratescorpions.jpg|thumb|right|240px|[[Pirate Scorpions]] — four of them will ruin your day.]]

Gamma is full of enemies that can and will destroy your squad without warning. Unlike Talsia where high deflection made most encounters manageable, Gamma has enemies specifically designed to punish the standard tank-everything build.

=== The Wasp ===
[[File:Dead_wasp.png|right|60px]]

The [[Wasp]] is the defining combat threat of Gamma's SE and NE quadrants. Every new Controller learns to respect them very quickly.

* '''Base speed: 225''' — faster than a standard Raven (base 150 speed). If you don't have Immobilisers on your Reaper or Enhanced Reaper, Wasps will drain you before you fire.
* '''Drain weapons''' — Wasps are equipped with powerful drain weapons that can strip reactor energy from your bots before they take a turn, effectively disabling them.
* '''DAX Pod deflection''' — Wasps in high-BM squads (37M+) are sometimes equipped with [[DAX Pod]] modules, which deflect drain back at the drainer. This can make your Reaper's drain less effective.
* '''Up to 6 Wasps per encounter''' — at very high BM, you can face a squad of 6 Wasps simultaneously. This is almost always unwinnable unless you have extreme drain coverage or multiple [[Pneumatron|Pneu Reactors]] to absorb the drain.

'''Counters:'''
# '''Immobiliser on every drain bot''' — equip at least 1 [[Syphon Immobiliser]] on each Raven/Reaper. At base 150 speed with Immobiliser, you can target and drain 2+ Wasps before they act.
# '''Vamper mercs''' — [[Vamper]] mercs are Reaper-type units that add drain coverage against multiple Wasps simultaneously. Essential for SE patrols.
# '''Lower your BM''' — keeping BM around 20–30M significantly reduces the number of Wasps per encounter.
# '''Kill or drain Wasps first''' — set targeting priority to the fastest/most dangerous units; kill Wasps with weapons if drain isn't fast enough.

{{MessageBox
| header = BM and Wasps
| text   = Keeping your squad BM close to 20–30M is the single most effective way to control Wasp encounters. At 37M+ BM you will regularly face 4–6 Wasps. At 20–25M BM, encounters typically include 2–3 Wasps, which is manageable with standard drain coverage.
}}

=== Pirate Scorpions ===
[[File:Piratescorpions.jpg|right|80px]]

[[Pirate Scorpion|Pirate Scorpions]] are elite Pirate units found primarily in the NW and outer space regions. A squad of '''4 Pirate Scorpions''' is one of the most dangerous encounters in Gamma.

* Their combined drain deflection was originally so high (29,400 deflection vs. ~29,250 Rayden crit drain) that they were literally unbeatable in a reasonable KC budget.
* Their loadout has since been adjusted (DAX Pods replaced with [[Gravity Hydro Booster]] modules) to bring drain deflection to a manageable level — but they remain very dangerous.
* '''Withdraw if your drain cannot break their shields in 1–2 turns.'''

=== Ex-Feds Special Operations ===
[[File:Gammapatrolsquad2.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Ex-Feds patrol the NW — their Special Ops squads have extreme drain deflection.]]

Ex-Feds Special Operations squads in the NW are walker-type units with very high deflection from Uplink Trucks. A well-equipped Ex-Feds Special Ops squad can '''instantly destroy Ravens''' if it outpaces your squad and fires first.

* Treat these like Talsia's True Guard — check the squad composition before committing.
* If there are multiple Uplink Trucks: withdraw unless you're confident your drain can break the shields fast.

=== Praetorian Recon ===
[[File:Forcereconscreen2.jpg|right|80px]]

[[Praetorian]] Recon units are elite Praetorian squads with extremely high fire rates — recorded instances of '''2,275+ fire rate'''. They deal enormous damage per turn.

* Always check the squad composition when entering SE or NE patrols.
* Against standard Praetorian patrols: fine.
* Against a Praetorian Recon squad: '''be very sure your deflection and shields can handle it, or withdraw immediately.'''

=== YF-95 Interceptors ===

The YF-95 Interceptors are described in-game as "the elite of the elite among Praetorian squads." Encountering them unexpectedly is a death sentence for an underprepared squad.
* '''Withdraw on sight unless you are confident.'''

=== Lava Reapers (SW) ===

[[Lava Reaper|Lava Reapers]] in the SW are fire-variant Reapers with high drain output. In cave fights, they appear alongside [[Sentinel|Sentinels]] and [[Bulwark|Bulwarks]].
* These fights take 3–4 KC each with standard drain. Additional [[Rayden Device|Raydens]] can reduce this to 2 KC.
* Max 2 Lava Reapers in a single encounter (post-patch limit).

=== The Space Monster ===

A unique, very dangerous enemy encountered in outer space in the NW. It has been described as the game's version of a "jumpscare" — an unexpected encounter with a single powerful entity. '''Withdraw immediately if encountered unprepared.'''

