== Key Mechanics to Understand ==

=== BM Management ===

Unlike Talsia, Gamma actively penalises high BM:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Total BM !! XP Multiplier
|-
| ≤ 30,000,000 || 100% (no penalty)
|-
| 30–35M || 90%
|-
| 35–40M || 80%
|-
| 40–45M || 70%
|-
| 45–50M || 60%
|-
| > 50M || 50%
|}

Target '''20–30M BM''' for the best experience-per-KC ratio. This also keeps enemy squad sizes manageable (fewer Wasps per encounter).

=== Merc Persistence ===

Gamma mercs are '''persistent''' — unlike Talsia where mercs are hired per mission and released afterwards, a Gamma merc stays with your squad until:
* It dies in combat (and is lost permanently for the patrol)
* You return to the Workshop

This means:
* '''Merc deaths are expensive''' — losing a full Custodian + Nightowl stack to a bad fight means losing thousands of Accolades.
* '''Choose fights carefully.''' There is no shame in withdrawing when your mercs are at risk.
* '''Mercs being alive at the end of patrol is a good sign''' you managed the patrol well.

=== Reinforcement Call Risk (SE) ===

When patrolling the SE, a '''Call for Reinforcements''' option appears. The outcome is:
* '''5% chance''' — receive free reinforcement mercs
* '''35% chance''' — the call is intercepted; enemy ambush incoming ('''use this option very cautiously''')
* ~60% — no response

=== 100-Ton Pirate Aggression Threshold ===

After stealing '''100+ tons of Meteorite Iron''' from SE Praetorian Mining Facilities cumulatively across all patrols, the Space Pirates start '''pre-draining and pre-damaging''' your squad at the start of every encounter. This "head start" penalty makes all subsequent Gamma patrols harder. [[DAX Pod]] modules help mitigate reactor pre-drain.

=== Quest Information Is Set-Specific and Randomised ===

Every set, quest keys are regenerated:
* Knight names (for PMC quest)
* City names (for PMC and Enhanced Reaper quests)
* Brotherhood door codes

These are different between accounts and between sets. '''Never assume last set's info applies.'''

