== General Tips ==

=== Going First is Everything ===
Gamma combat is decided by initiative. If the enemy goes first and you're facing Wasps or a high-fire-rate Praetorian squad, your bots will be drained/destroyed before they act. Prioritise:
* Speed upgrades on Ravens
* [[Hyper Drive]] on Hornets
* [[Nightowl]] mercs for squad speed bonus
* [[Syphon Immobiliser|Immobilisers]] on drain bots — they neutralise fast enemies before they act

=== Accolade Starvation ===
New Gamma players are almost always Accolade-starved in the early patrols. Mercs are expensive; the NW is your best source of Accolades (Ex-Feds Outposts: 100–200 each; Destroyers: +25 TRP, +15 Accolades; True Guard: Accolades in Gamma). '''Farm the NW before committing to heavy merc-loadout patrols.'''

=== Don't Fast-Click ===
Gamma events contain quest information, hints, and lore that are '''permanently lost''' if skipped. Missing the Knight's name from an SE Outpost means spending KC finding another one (10% chance per outpost). Missing the door code from the NE Temple can block the entire PMC quest. '''Read every event. Take notes.'''

=== Meteorite Mining — Know the Threshold ===
Stealing Meteorite Iron from SE Praetorian Mining Facilities gives enormous experience and Mirons — but after '''100+ cumulative tons stolen''', Pirates begin pre-draining and pre-damaging your squad before every encounter. Plan your mining around this threshold; equip [[DAX Pod|DAX Pods]] accordingly once you cross it.

=== The Casino and Market — Skip Them ===
The SE Casino and Market are event encounters. The Casino is ''not'' favourable on average (it's designed to eat your resources). The Market can sell [[Pneumatron|Pneu Reactors]] for '''10,000 Accolades''' — an extremely high price that is rarely worth it early on. Avoid these events unless you have surplus Accolades to spare. (Going to the Casino is an adventure, but you've been warned. 😛)

=== Follow the Quest Breadcrumbs ===
Many Gamma encounters are connected to quest chains in non-obvious ways. The [[Brotherhood of the Chosen]] quest spans all four quadrants and requires encountering specific events in a specific order. If something seems like it might be a quest trigger — it probably is. '''Don't skip it.'''

=== You Will Die ===
Unlike Talsia's late-game endgame, where a good squad can run almost indefinitely, Gamma is designed to punish overconfidence. Losing bots to a bad fight, or losing an expensive merc to a misclick, is part of the experience. The zone is balanced around Controllers who are cautious, strategic, and willing to withdraw when a fight isn't going well.

'''Withdraw early and often when in doubt.''' The KC cost of withdrawing is always less than the KC cost of losing a bot.

